# XCP Privacy Policy

## Introduction
At XCP Photography, we value the privacy of our clients and are committed to protecting any personal data that we collect during our engagements. 

## Photographer's Name
All references to the photographer in this document refer to Xavier Clarke, who will be delivering high-quality photographs and services to ensure a satisfactory client experience.

## Data Processing by External Team Members
In the course of delivering our photographic services, we may engage external team members, such as videographers, makeup artists, and other professionals. These external team members may have access to client data when brought in for specific shoots. We ensure that these individuals are also bound by strict data protection standards to protect your information as rigorously as we do.

## Image Delivery
Images will be delivered via private SmugMug galleries. Clients will have the option to password-protect these galleries to limit access to their photographs. 

## SEO Considerations
We prioritize SEO best practices in our workflow, ensuring that all delivered content is optimized with appropriate keywords/tags—both literal and figurative—to enhance online discoverability. Alt text will be included for all images to enhance accessibility. 

## Professional Editing Workflow
We maintain a professional editing workflow that ensures each image is carefully edited to meet our high standards. This workflow guarantees that every photograph is presented beautifully and accurately.

## Delivery Methods
Each shoot may involve various delivery methods tailored to the unique needs of the client. We aim to provide customized services that accommodate different preferences. 

## Conclusion
Your trust is vital to us at XCP Photography. By engaging our services, you can rest assured that your privacy and data protection are our top priorities.